{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I speak at high schools and other places today, I say discrimination is one of the world's greatest evils, responsible for millions of deaths.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I point out that none of us have a choice of what religion or what race we belong to.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "None of us volunteered to come into the world so you're stuck with whatever we happen to be, whether you're a Muslim or Catholic or Baptist or black or white.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No one could help it, so why should we discriminate against people who had no choice about what their color or race or religion is?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I think when you see those concentration camps, you see discrimination-- --at the lowest depth of degradation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One thing I've never seen mentioned hardly at all is the fact that there was another group of people who were discriminated against even worse the Jewish people were, and those were the gypsies.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The gypsies were rounded up and exterminated offhand in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they were just-- many of the Jewish people, at least the younger Jewish men, served in labor camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So thousands of them survived by serving in the labor camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The policy in Nazi Germany was for women and children to be executed promptly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were considered worthless.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were no children in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were-- and the older people were singled out for extermination.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But many in the younger group, say 16 to 30, survived because they were put in labor camps, although younger ones also were killed in the concentration camps at Auschwitz and Buchenwald are two of the worst that come to mind.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the gypsies, they weren't even put in labor camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were just killed out of hand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There's nobody to speak for the gypsies, you see.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
